    </exercisegroup>
    <exercise>
      <p>    Now use what you learned in the previous problems to show that
      <md>
        <mrow>\limit{x}{1}{\frac{x^a-1}{x^b-1}}=\frac{a}{b}</mrow>
      </md>
      (Assume <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> are both positive integers.)
      </p>
